city.label: Gurgaon
city.description:
Here’s a synopsis of Gurgaon for all those who wish to better understand this booming corporate hub in NCR.

One of the most sought after real estate investment destinations in the country, Gurgaon is the best example of rapid urbanization in Northern India. Once a small town in the Indian state of Haryana comprising large farmlands owned by the locals, Gurgaon has witnessed tremendous development ever since automotive major Maruti Suzuki laid its plant here in the year 1970. Today, it has hundreds of organizations operating in various parts of the city. It spans over an area of 457 square kilometres, with a population close to a million residing in it.

The erstwhile agricultural stretch of Gurgaon today boasts of imposing and futuristic structures where numerous workplaces thrive, and have earned it the title of having the third highest per-capita income in India. Several global companies have recognized Gurgaon as a highly feasible outsourcing hub, and that has led to the surge in commercial spaces within the city, although it still suffers from weak infrastructure and facilities. Some of the well-known organizations that operate from Gurgaon include GE, Bank of America, IBM, Google, Coca-Cola, Siemens, Ford, Microsoft and Orange Business Services. It is important to note here that most of the organizations operating in Gurgaon rely on their own arrangements for power and other basic facilities, as the city itself does not offer adequate supply of the same. That said, more than half of the Fortune 500 companies still choose Gurgaon as the apt location to set up their offices in India.

One of the main reasons for the rapid development of Gurgaon has been its close proximity to the national capital – New . Gurgaon is located just about 20 kilometres from the Indira Gandhi International Airport, and 25 kilometres from Connaught Place, located in the heart of New . The National Highway no. 8 gives Gurgaon easy access to all important points of interest in Delhi as well as other upcoming suburbs in Haryana like Manesar and Bhiwadi.

More about the city

Also called the Millenium City, Gurgaon boasts of several skyscrapers towering above the city’s skyline and several residential complexes being launched one after the other. The past decade has witnessed massive construction across all parts of Gurgaon, most notably along prime areas like City, Golf Course Road and Sohna Road.

With more and more job opportunities drawing professionals from across the country, there has been a surge in the demand for residential as well as commercial spaces in Gurgaon, and these have led to modernistic structures coming up in almost every part of the city. Apart from Gurgaon itself, the rapid urbanization has also spread to nearby areas like Bhiwadi and Sohna. As these suburbs expand and become one with Gurgaon, the city looks forward to even more development in the years to come.

Certain areas of Gurgaon (mostly the corporate hubs) enjoy better means of public transport via the Metro rail which connects the capital city with five important areas in Gurgaon along its route. These stations include Guru Dronacharya, Sikanderpur, MG Road, IFFCO Chowk and HUDA City Centre. Recently, the first phase of Rapid Metro Rail has also been launched in Gurgaon, which is the only privately funded metro rail in the world. The Rapid Metro Rail connects various important areas within Gurgaon with each other, and is also linked to the Metro rail.

Villages in Gurgaon

Apart from the city, Gurgaon is also one of the 21 different districts in Haryana. The main city happens to be the administrative headquarters of the district of Gurgaon, which has several tehsils including Gurgaon, Sohna, Farukh Nagar, Manesar and Pataudi. These tehsils cover villages like Gwal Pahari, Chakkarpur, Jharsa, Nathupur, Khandsa and Sidhrawali. The total area of Gurgaon district is well over 1000 square kilometres.

Schools and Colleges

Gurgaon has plenty of government schools that are run by the Haryana Board of School Education, and also several high end private schools which offer world class education. Some important schools located in Gurgaon include Public School (DPS), Shri Ram Public School, GD Goenka School, DAV Public School, The Heritage School and Amity International.

There are also several colleges offering higher education to students who come from Gurgaon as well as other parts of the country and sometimes across the globe. Popular colleges in Gurgaon include Institute of Technology, Amity Business School, Apeejay College of Engineering, IILM, Algol School of Management and Technology and Management Development Institute , among many others.

Shopping Malls and Recreation

There are several malls and recreational hubs in Gurgaon which offer ample entertainment opportunities with ultramodern facilities. There are more than 25 shopping malls in Gurgaon as of now, and all of them offer countless shopping avenues, entertainment centres and food courts. Important malls in Gurgaon include the Mall, Mega Mall, Mall and Central Mall.

Apart from shopping centres, there are also a handful of other entertainment avenues including the larger than life Kingdom Of Dreams, which features exclusive musicals, cultural events and a fabulous eat street.

There are also botanical parks and performing arts centres in Gurgaon, which are located in various parts of the city.

Real Estate in Gurgaon

Real Estate in Gurgaon has been witnessing rapid development over the past decade, and there are several residential as well as commercial properties launched each year. Being well-developed and enjoying significant value appreciation, real estate in Gurgaon is the preferred choice for homebuyers and investors alike.

locality.label: Sector 77
locality.description: In Gurgaon, Sector 77 is one of the popular localities in suburb NH8. Sector 70, Sector 70A, Sector 72, Sector 73, Sector 76, Sector 78, Sector 79, Sector 80, Sector 81 and Sector 82 are located close to Sector 77. Some of the key projects offering properties in this locality are Winter Hills by Umang Realtech and Palm Hills by Emaar MGF. The property in Sector 77 are build in areas ranging 1,342 sq ft to 2,077 sq ft. with bedroom configurations of 2 BHK, 3 BHK and 4 BHK. Sector 77 has many well known Hospitals. Key hospitals to this locality are Shri Balaji Hospital, DLF Primary Health Center, Krishna Hospital and SRS Hospital. Property starting at 87.9 Lacs are available in Sector 77 on Proptiger. You can find 2 under construction projects in Sector 77 from different builders. Winter Hills by Umang Realtech is available at lowest rate of Rs. 6,350 per sq ft in Sector 77, whereas Winter Hills by Umang Realtech is available at highest rate of Rs. 6,550 per sq ft.

builder.name: Umang Realtech
builder.description:
Umang Realtech is a leading realty company founded by Mr. B.K. Uppal who holds office as the Chairman of the company while Mr. Manish Uppal serves as its Managing Director. The company specializes in luxurious and high quality projects and delivers exquisitely designed residential units to buyers. The company is headquartered at Nehru Place in New Delhi and also has another office at Bangalore. The portfolio of completed property by Umang Realtech covers almost 5.7 and 5 million sq ft in Delhi and Bangalore respectively. The company also has many other projects in the pipeline which cover a total area of 13.2 million sq ft cumulatively.

Umang Realtech is a joint venture between Uppal Housing Pvt Limited and Indus Capital Partners, LLC (USA) which is one of Asia’s leading investment firms. The name of the company itself translates into enthusiasm and this philosophy is directly visible through its approach to project planning and execution where the company’s passion to satisfy customers with life’s finest thing is aptly manifested through its ventures. The company has a customer base exceeding 2500 at present and operates in several areas like Delhi, Faridabad, Gurgaon and Bahadurgarh.

Unique Selling Point:

The company operates on the basis of several core values and these include commitment towards customer satisfaction and continual innovation and evolution. The company’s USPs includes architectural brilliance, innovation, professionalism and efficiency in addition to contemporary, cost competitive real estate solutions. The company is focused on maximizing returns to all its customers, investors and associates with a conscientious and value based approach to projects.

Landmark Projects:

The landmark projects helmed by the company include Summer Palms at Sector 86 Faridabad which offers 2 and 3 BHK apartments and Monsoon Breeze at Sector 78 in Gurgaon. Other premium projects include Monsoon Breeze Phase 2 at Sector 78 in Gurgaon, Winter Hills at Shanti Park, Dwarka which offers 2, 3 and 4 BHK apartments and also Summer Palms at Bahadurgarh.

data.name: Winter Hills
data.offerDesc: Pay 10% Now & No EMI for 18 Months
data.description: Umang Realtech Winter Hills is a residential complex in Sector 77 in Gurgaon. The complex has 2 and 3BHK apartments on offer that cost between Rs87.2 lakh and 1.3 crore. The complex is awaiting completion shortly and has 724 units available through resale and the developer. The size of the flats range from 1342 to 2077 sq. ft. Spread over 16 acres, the community shall have numerous amenities on offer which include swimming pool, gymnasium, sports facilities, car parking, jogging track and landscaped gardens. Umang Realtech is a reputed property developer of Gurgaon, having worked on six properties so far. Five of their projects are under construction. Sector 77 is positioned quite strategically as the Hero Honda and IFFCO Chowk are 7 and 14 kilometres from here respectively.
